  • [ - ] Zoltan - member since 15-Feb-20

    I wonder if Conte knows how to play his team against a parked bus? Most teams have no clue that in such situations it is essential to move the ball quickly with a one-touch passing game especially after turnovers AND alternate between 3 attacking schemes: 1. go down the wings (most effective) and instead of centering the ball (for which the defense is prepared) you pass it backwards to create a shooting situation for a teammate arriving in the second wave (after the forwards playing a decoy inside the penalty box area). 2. make the defense guess by attacking sometimes directly, vertically into the centerforward running in the free channels (either with a flat ball, or over the top), so that he can hang on to the ball and pass it back for a long distance shot once again through the middle, AND 3. allow every once in a while your opponent to possess the ball to lure him into a false sense of security and then suddenly put a pressure onto your opponent to produce an unexpected turnover
